<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06270154 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06270154 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  US; PROFESSIONAL; GOLF; CLUB; AUTO; ACCIDENT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  America's Ryder Cup plans were scrambled Wednesday night when a three-caraccident injured team member Steve Pate.;   Pate suffered rib injuries after aconvoy of limousines became involved in a three-car rear-end collision on theway to a formal dinner in Charleston, PGA officials said.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  U.S. RYDER CUP TEAM IN CAR ACCIDENT  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Pate and Shannon Pavin, the wife of golfer Corey Pavin, were treated andreleased from St. Francis Xavier Hospital in Charleston. A nursing supervisorsaid Pate had abdominal pain and Pavin had an elbow injury, but neither hadany broken bones or major injuries.;   Pate, who played his way onto the teamin the last qualifying tournament, was expected to be a central figure on theU.S. team.;   &quot;I had him penciled in to play (the maximum) five matches,&quot; U.S.captain Dave Stockton said. &quot;I simply don't know what I'm going to do now. Itwill involve a lot of juggling. It could be that he will be available onSunday&quot; for the closing 12 singles matches. &quot;But I probably won't have himuntil then.&quot;;   If Pate is unable to play, Tim Simpson would step in as thefirst alternate.;   The biennial matches between the United States and Europebegin Friday at Kiawah Island's Ocean Course.;   According to the officials, acaravan of cars was bringing the U.S. team on the 25-mile trip from KiawahIsland to Charleston.;   About five miles south of Charleston, the officialssaid an unlit police vehicle moved into the caravan in front of a lit policeescort vehicle. The escort vehicle braked, setting off the accident.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Kiawah Island, S.C.  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910926  </P